<article class="itinerary-popup-content">
  <p>
    Fall in love with Krakow on a carefully curated 4-day journey that blends heritage, reflection,
    and iconic landmarks of southern Poland.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 1: Italy / Krakow</h3>
  <p>
    Arrival at Krakow airport. Transfer by coach to the hotel, check-in, dinner, and overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 2: Krakow / Wieliczka</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. In the morning, guided visit of Krakow's historic center, listed as a
    UNESCO World Heritage site and one of the world's most valuable architectural complexes. The
    program includes Wawel Hill with the Royal Castle and Cathedral, the Old Town Market Square,
    the Cloth Hall, and St. Mary's Basilica. Lunch. In the afternoon, excursion to Wieliczka to
    visit Europe's oldest salt mine, with unique chambers, chapels carved in salt, and underground
    lakes. Return to Krakow, dinner, and overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 3: Auschwitz-Birkenau / Krakow</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. Departure to Oświęcim (Auschwitz) for a guided tour of the former Nazi
    concentration camp Auschwitz-Birkenau, a profound witness to the tragedy of the Holocaust.
    Lunch. In the afternoon, visit Kazimierz, Krakow's historic Jewish quarter, home to a renowned
    Jewish community for centuries. Dinner and overnight stay.
  </p>

  <h3>Day 4: Krakow / Italy</h3>
  <p>
    Breakfast at the hotel. Transfer to Krakow airport for the return flight to Italy.
  </p>
</article>
